HEADWORD: Catchdrain
<hw>Catch"drain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A ditch or drain
along the side of a hill to catch the surface water; also, a ditch at
the side of a canal to catch the surplus water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catcher</ent>⟦br⟧
